'''Floating mines''' were simplistic, suicidal [[Droid/Legends|droids]]. They were essentially mines capable of moving equipped with sensors, [[Repulsorlift/Legends|repulsorlifts]] and sometimes with [[Stealth field generator/Legends|stealth field generators]]. When they detected a target, they floated into its proximity and exploded. [[G0-T0]] employed a number of floating mines to guard his [[Visionary|Droid Yacht]]. They were also encountered in the antechamber of the [[Airlock/Legends|airlock]] from the fuel depot in the [[Peragus Mining Facility]] by the [[Meetra Surik|Jedi Exile]]. The [[HK-50 series assassin droid|HK-50]] droid that watched the Exile during her journey to [[Peragus II]] also deployed floating mines when it confronted her. These particular mines were equipped with stealth field generators.

